\subsubsection{Responsibility Species}
A Pennsylvania-responsibility species (the term may also refer to subspecies or varieties) is one for which Pennsylvania plays a key role in sustaining its global security by hosting at least 10\% of its North American population or encompassing at least 25\% of its North American range. (PABS http://www.pabiologicalsurvey.org/pennsylvania-responsibility.html)

