Principles of Spatial Conservation Planning
\begin{itemize}
\item Efficiency – compactness and spatial arrangement
\item Flexibility – alternative solutions
\item Complementarity – the gain in diversity achieved when adding that site to a set of other sites
\item Irreplaceability – (selection frequency)
\end{itemize}

